By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) –  The latest COVID-19 report from Nigeria has it that Lagos State – the epicentre of the novel virus infection accounted for 142 patients out the 236 new cases confirmed by the Nigeria Centre for Disease Control on Wednesday. According to the report released by the health agency via it’s twitter handle, other states where infections were recorded are;Ogun-19Kaduna-15FCT-14Imo-14Rivers-14Plateau-6Katsina-3Ekiti-2Jigawa-2Oyo-2Cross River-1Kano-1Taraba-1 The report further informed that the total confirmed cases has now risen to 65,693 out of which 61,457 have been discharged. The NCDC also added that 1,163 deaths have been recorded in Nigeria since the index case was reported early this year. See below the total confirmed cases for all the 36 states of the federation including the FCT: By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) -   The Nigeria Centre for Disease Control on Wednesday said it has confirmed 111 new cases of COVID-19 in Nigeria. This new cases, it said, brought total Confirmed COVID-19 infections in Nigeria to 57,724 out of which 48,985 patients have been discharged. According to… September 24, 2020 In "Top Stories" By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) -  Lagos State, the epicentre of COVID-19 pandemic in Nigeria recorded 74 infections as the Nigeria Centre for Disease Control confirmed 187 new cases on Tuesday. Releasing this report via it's twitter handle, the NCDC said the other twelve states that reported cases are;… September 30, 2020 In "Top Stories" By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata be Post) -  The Nigeria Centre for Disease Control said it confirmed 119 new cases of COVID-19 in Nigeria on with Lagos State, the epicentre of the pandemic accounting for 77 Infections. The report released via it's twitter handle said the other five states that… October 27, 2020 In "Top Stories"